Tim Sherwood is the leading contender to replace sacked Alan Irvine with West Bromwich Albion keen to make an appointment by the weekend.

The former Tottenham Hotspur head coach came close to landing the Hawthorns job last summer but talks collapsed over wages and Sherwood’s desire to bring in assistants Les Ferdinand and Chris Ramsey.

Those hurdles could be overcome on this occasion with the futures of current assistants Keith Downing and Rob Kelly uncertain. 

