Chairman Jeremy Peace, who fired both Steve Clarke and Pepe Mel last season, had been keen to make the summer appointment of Irvine work and knows the players have been fully behind his methods. 

But after travelling fans subjected Irvine to a barrage of abuse at the end of Sunday's 2-0 defeat at Stoke City, the 56-year-old's time at the Hawthorns has come to an end. 

Irvine has overseen a dismal run of results that have seen West Brom win just once in the last nine Premier League games, leaving the club one point above the relegation zone.

 

